definitions.definition: Music with multiple rhythmic elements played simultaneously.
A rhythm or set of rhythms performed as part of a piece of music with multiple rhythmic elements played simultaneously, typically equally spaced in time and coprime .

main_definition: ( uncountable , music ) Music with multiple rhythmic elements played simultaneously.
secondary_definitions: ( countable , music ) A rhythm or set of rhythms performed as part of a piece of music with multiple rhythmic elements played simultaneously, typically equally spaced in time and coprime .
( countable , music ) Music containing such a rhythm.
